We're sorry. Your call cannot
be completed as dialed.

822
01:16:43,818 --> 01:16:46,946
If you need assistance,
please call the operator.

823
01:17:04,208 --> 01:17:06,040
Yes, it's me.

824
01:17:06,244 --> 01:17:07,677
Thank God.

825
01:17:12,351 --> 01:17:14,115
Did you find anything?

826
01:17:14,321 --> 01:17:17,051
No. Nothing at all.

827
01:17:17,658 --> 01:17:20,822
I didn't see one goddamn thing.

828
01:17:23,565 --> 01:17:27,057
You went into the room Danny said?
To 237?

829
01:17:27,269 --> 01:17:28,828
Yes, I did.

830
01:17:29,306 --> 01:17:31,103
And you didn't see anything at all?

831
01:17:31,308 --> 01:17:33,299
Absolutely nothing.

832
01:17:33,510 --> 01:17:34,772
How is he?

833
01:17:34,978 --> 01:17:36,776
He's still asleep.

834
01:17:37,181 --> 01:17:38,307
Good.

835
01:17:44,122 --> 01:17:47,216
I'm sure he'll be himself again
in the morning.

836
01:17:51,699 --> 01:17:54,190
Are you sure it was the right room?

837
01:17:54,401 --> 01:17:57,564
I mean, maybe Danny made a mistake.

838
01:17:57,771 --> 01:18:00,138
He must have gone in that room.

839
01:18:00,342 --> 01:18:03,004
The door was open,
the lights were on.

840
01:18:05,647 --> 01:18:07,980
I just don't understand it.

841
01:18:12,322 --> 01:18:15,349
What about those bruises
on his neck?

842
01:18:17,529 --> 01:18:19,861
Somebody did that to him.

843
01:18:28,140 --> 01:18:29,573
I think...

844
01:18:31,245 --> 01:18:33,805
...he did it to himself.

845
01:18:39,821 --> 01:18:41,049
No.

846
01:18:41,723 --> 01:18:43,748
That's not possible.

847
01:18:49,066 --> 01:18:52,729
Once you rule out his version
of what happened...

848
01:18:52,970 --> 01:18:55,565
...there is no other explanation.

849
01:18:56,041 --> 01:18:57,372
Is there?

850
01:18:59,744 --> 01:19:02,646
It wouldn't be that different
from the episode...

851
01:19:02,848 --> 01:19:06,215
...that he had before
we came up here.

852
01:19:06,419 --> 01:19:07,647
Would it?

853
01:19:15,563 --> 01:19:18,556
Whatever the explanation is...

854
01:19:22,004 --> 01:19:23,403
...I think we...

855
01:19:23,606 --> 01:19:26,337
...have to get Danny out of here.

856
01:19:31,115 --> 01:19:32,947
Get him out of here?

857
01:19:37,122 --> 01:19:38,851
You mean...

858
01:19:39,891 --> 01:19:41,860
...just leave the hotel?

859
01:19:50,839 --> 01:19:52,306
It is so...

860
01:19:52,507 --> 01:19:54,941
...typical of you to create
a problem like this...

861
01:19:55,143 --> 01:19:57,669
...when I finally have a chance
to accomplish something!

862
01:19:57,880 --> 01:20:00,440
When I'm really into my work!

863
01:20:00,650 --> 01:20:04,610
I could really write my own ticket
if I went back now, couldn't I?

864
01:20:04,821 --> 01:20:08,552
Shoveling out driveways,
work in a car wash.

865
01:20:08,759 --> 01:20:10,852
Any of that appeal to you?

866
01:20:12,064 --> 01:20:14,760
I have let you fuck up my life
so far...

867
01:20:14,967 --> 01:20:18,596
...but I am not going to let you
fuck this up.

868
01:21:36,529 --> 01:21:38,828
Good evening. Forest Service.

869
01:21:39,399 --> 01:21:40,832
My name is Dick Hallorann.

870
01:21:41,034 --> 01:21:43,468
I'm the head chef at
the Overlook Hotel.

871
01:21:43,670 --> 01:21:45,798
Good evening.
What can I do for you?

872
01:21:46,007 --> 01:21:49,568
I've been trying to make
an urgent phone call up there...

873
01:21:49,778 --> 01:21:53,077
...but the operator said
that the phone lines are down.

874
01:21:53,283 --> 01:21:56,878
A lot of lines around here
are down due to the storm.

875
01:21:57,087 --> 01:21:59,749
I hate to put you through
any trouble...

876
01:21:59,956 --> 01:22:03,188
...but there's a family up there
all by themselves with a young kid.

877
01:22:03,394 --> 01:22:05,055
And with this storm
and everything...

878
01:22:05,263 --> 01:22:08,164
...I'd appreciate it if you'd give
them a call on your radio...

879
01:22:08,366 --> 01:22:10,358
...just to see if
everything's okay.

880
01:22:10,869 --> 01:22:12,166
I'll be glad to do that.

881
01:22:12,371 --> 01:22:15,169
Why don't you call me back
in about 20 minutes?

882
01:22:15,375 --> 01:22:17,401
Thank you very much.
I'll do that.

883
01:22:17,611 --> 01:22:19,044
All right, sir.

884
01:22:39,369 --> 01:22:41,338
Good evening, Mr. Torrance.

885
01:22:41,539 --> 01:22:43,006
Good evening.

886
01:23:07,569 --> 01:23:09,036
Hi, Lloyd.

887
01:23:09,238 --> 01:23:11,103
Been away, but now I'm back.

888
01:23:11,374 --> 01:23:13,103
Good evening, Mr. Torrance.

889
01:23:13,776 --> 01:23:14,765
It's good to see you.

890
01:23:14,978 --> 01:23:17,640
It's good to be back, Lloyd.

891
01:23:18,282 --> 01:23:20,012
What'll it be, sir?

892
01:23:20,819 --> 01:23:23,083
Hair of the dog that bit me.

893
01:23:24,489 --> 01:23:26,150
Bourbon on the rocks.

894
01:23:26,993 --> 01:23:28,392
That'll do her.

895
01:23:41,910 --> 01:23:44,175
No charge to you, Mr. Torrance.

896
01:23:45,614 --> 01:23:47,582
No charge?

897
01:23:48,217 --> 01:23:50,209
Your money's no good here.

898
01:23:55,859 --> 01:23:57,588
Orders from the house.

899
01:24:00,799 --> 01:24:03,290
Orders from the house.

900
01:24:06,539 --> 01:24:08,530
Drink up, Mr. Torrance.

901
01:24:10,743 --> 01:24:15,272
I'm the kind of man likes to know
who's buying their drinks, Lloyd.

902
01:24:17,585 --> 01:24:20,520
It's not a matter that concerns you,
Mr. Torrance.

903
01:24:20,722 --> 01:24:22,657
At least, not at this point.

904
01:24:27,463 --> 01:24:29,864
Anything you say, Lloyd.

905
01:24:30,300 --> 01:24:32,291
Anything you say.

906
01:24:45,285 --> 01:24:47,753
Oh, dear! I'm so sorry, sir.

907
01:24:48,855 --> 01:24:50,322
Oh, dear. Oh, dear.

908
01:24:50,523 --> 01:24:53,084
I've made an awful mess
of your jacket, sir.

909
01:24:54,328 --> 01:24:57,957
That's all right.
I've got plenty of jackets.

910
01:24:58,166 --> 01:25:00,965
I'm afraid it's advocaat, sir.
It tends to stain.

911
01:25:01,170 --> 01:25:02,296
Advocaat, is it?

912
01:25:02,505 --> 01:25:04,666
Yes, sir.
I think the best thing...

913
01:25:04,874 --> 01:25:07,069
...is to come along
to the gentlemen's room...

914
01:25:07,276 --> 01:25:09,802
...and we'll get
some water to it, sir.

915
01:25:10,647 --> 01:25:13,946
Looks like you might have got a
spot of it on yourself...

916
01:25:14,151 --> 01:25:15,140
...Jeevesy old boy.

917
01:25:15,352 --> 01:25:18,516
That doesn't matter, sir.
You're the important one.

918
01:25:18,824 --> 01:25:21,224
Awfully nice of you to say.

919
01:25:21,660 --> 01:25:24,528
Of course, I intended to change
my jacket this evening...

920
01:25:24,731 --> 01:25:26,995
...before the fish and
goose soiree.

921
01:25:27,200 --> 01:25:29,225
Very wise, sir. Very wise.

922
01:25:29,436 --> 01:25:30,767
Here. I'll just...

923
01:25:31,572 --> 01:25:33,836
...hold this for you there,
Jeevesy.

924
01:25:34,042 --> 01:25:35,839
Thank you, sir. Thank you.

925
01:25:36,878 --> 01:25:40,508
Let's see if we can improve this
with a little water, sir.

926
01:25:40,717 --> 01:25:41,979
All right. I'll just...

927
01:25:42,185 --> 01:25:46,383
...set my bourbon and advocaat
down right there.

928
01:25:46,956 --> 01:25:48,390
Won't keep you a moment.

929
01:25:48,592 --> 01:25:49,991
Fine.

930
01:25:53,064 --> 01:25:54,725
What do they call you,
Jeevesy?

931
01:25:54,933 --> 01:25:57,493
Grady, sir. Delbert Grady.

932
01:26:02,275 --> 01:26:03,106
Grady?

933
01:26:03,310 --> 01:26:04,641
Yes, sir.

934
01:26:05,813 --> 01:26:07,144
Delbert Grady.

935
01:26:07,347 --> 01:26:08,871
That's right, sir.

936
01:26:17,592 --> 01:26:19,026
Mr. Grady...

937
01:26:19,796 --> 01:26:21,889
...haven't I seen you
somewhere before?

938
01:26:22,099 --> 01:26:24,795
Why, no, sir. I don't believe so.

939
01:26:31,843 --> 01:26:33,674
It's coming off now, sir.

940
01:26:38,617 --> 01:26:40,175
Mr. Grady...

941
01:26:41,689 --> 01:26:44,157
...weren't you once
the caretaker here?

942
01:26:44,358 --> 01:26:47,156
Why, no, sir. I don't believe so.

943
01:26:50,198 --> 01:26:53,531
You a married man, are you,
Mr. Grady?

944
01:26:53,735 --> 01:26:54,565
Yes, sir.

945
01:26:54,769 --> 01:26:58,035
I have a wife and
two daughters, sir.

946
01:26:59,075 --> 01:27:00,599
And...

947
01:27:02,279 --> 01:27:03,541
...where are they now?

948
01:27:03,747 --> 01:27:07,809
They're somewhere around.
I'm not quite sure at the moment.

949
01:27:18,497 --> 01:27:20,898
You were the caretaker here.

950
01:27:22,370 --> 01:27:24,361
I recognize you.

951
01:27:25,740 --> 01:27:28,801
I saw your picture
in the newspapers.

952
01:27:29,244 --> 01:27:31,007
You...

953
01:27:31,480 --> 01:27:35,007
...chopped your wife and daughter
up into little bits.

954
01:27:35,517 --> 01:27:36,917
And...

955
01:27:37,554 --> 01:27:39,488
...then you blew your brains out.

956
01:27:49,401 --> 01:27:51,164
That's strange, sir.

957
01:27:52,171 --> 01:27:54,901
I don't have any recollection
of that at all.

958
01:27:58,578 --> 01:28:00,444
Mr. Grady...

959
01:28:00,881 --> 01:28:04,214
...you were the caretaker here.

960
01:28:12,027 --> 01:28:14,791
I'm sorry to differ with you, sir.

961
01:28:16,666 --> 01:28:18,395
But you...

962
01:28:19,135 --> 01:28:20,966
...are the caretaker.

963
01:28:23,242 --> 01:28:26,143
You've always been the caretaker.

964
01:28:29,047 --> 01:28:30,879
I should know, sir.

965
01:28:32,318 --> 01:28:34,912
I've always been here.

966
01:28:53,142 --> 01:28:55,338
Did you know, Mr. Torrance...

967
01:28:55,579 --> 01:28:57,342
...that your son...

968
01:28:57,748 --> 01:29:00,444
...is attempting to bring
an outside party...

969
01:29:00,651 --> 01:29:02,847
...into this situation?

970
01:29:05,424 --> 01:29:07,119
Did you know that?

971
01:29:13,366 --> 01:29:15,459
He is, Mr. Torrance.

972
01:29:17,805 --> 01:29:18,965
Who?

973
01:29:21,208 --> 01:29:22,835
A nigger.

974
01:29:26,916 --> 01:29:28,315
A nigger?

975
01:29:31,054 --> 01:29:32,487
A nigger...

976
01:29:32,689 --> 01:29:33,782
...cook.

977
01:29:40,297 --> 01:29:41,560
How?

978
01:29:43,835 --> 01:29:45,598
Your son...

979
01:29:46,038 --> 01:29:48,837
...has a very great talent.

980
01:29:49,810 --> 01:29:53,302
I don't think you are aware
how great it is.

981
01:29:54,047 --> 01:29:57,279
But he is attempting to use
that very talent...

982
01:29:57,485 --> 01:29:59,453
...against your will.

983
01:30:07,997 --> 01:30:09,259
Well...

984
01:30:12,035 --> 01:30:15,096
...he is a very willful boy.

985
01:30:17,508 --> 01:30:19,909
Indeed he is, Mr. Torrance.

986
01:30:20,112 --> 01:30:23,013
A very willful boy.

987
01:30:23,215 --> 01:30:24,546
A rather...

988
01:30:24,750 --> 01:30:26,274
...naughty boy...

989
01:30:26,486 --> 01:30:29,684
...if I may be so bold, sir.

990
01:30:36,931 --> 01:30:38,694
It's his mother.

991
01:30:40,835 --> 01:30:42,302
She...

992
01:30:42,504 --> 01:30:44,496
...interferes.

993
01:30:47,611 --> 01:30:50,705
Perhaps they need a good...

994
01:30:50,914 --> 01:30:52,507
...talking-to.

995
01:30:52,950 --> 01:30:53,780
If...

996
01:30:53,985 --> 01:30:56,749
...you don't mind my saying so.

997
01:30:57,555 --> 01:30:59,183
Perhaps...

998
01:30:59,725 --> 01:31:01,420
...a bit more.

999
01:31:04,630 --> 01:31:05,858
My girls, sir...

1000
01:31:06,064 --> 01:31:09,865
...they didn't care for
the Overlook at first.

1001
01:31:10,538 --> 01:31:14,441
One of them actually stole
a pack of matches...

1002
01:31:14,643 --> 01:31:17,305
...and tried to burn it down.

1003
01:31:18,380 --> 01:31:20,041
But I...

1004
01:31:20,248 --> 01:31:22,216
...corrected them, sir.

1005
01:31:23,553 --> 01:31:27,683
And when my wife tried to prevent me
from doing my duty...

1006
01:31:27,891 --> 01:31:29,153
...I...

1007
01:31:30,161 --> 01:31:32,254
...corrected her.

1008
01:31:46,513 --> 01:31:48,447
We have the Snowcat.

1009
01:31:51,853 --> 01:31:53,617
If the weather breaks...

1010
01:31:53,822 --> 01:31:55,585
...we might just be able...

1011
01:31:55,791 --> 01:31:57,656
...to get down the mountain.

1012
01:32:00,529 --> 01:32:03,499
I could call
the forest rangers first...

1013
01:32:03,700 --> 01:32:04,997
...and...

1014
01:32:05,335 --> 01:32:07,200
...tell them that we're coming...

1015
01:32:07,571 --> 01:32:08,731
....so that...

1016
01:32:08,939 --> 01:32:13,036
...they could start searching
for us in case we didn't make it.

1017
01:32:16,816 --> 01:32:18,977
And if Jack won't come with us...

1018
01:32:21,454 --> 01:32:25,186
...I'll just have to tell him that
we're going by ourselves.

1019
01:32:25,392 --> 01:32:27,360
That's all there is to it.

1020
01:32:28,730 --> 01:32:30,220
Redrum.

1021
01:32:31,199 --> 01:32:32,861
Redrum.

1022
01:32:44,114 --> 01:32:45,274
What's the matter, hon?

1023
01:32:45,482 --> 01:32:46,380
Redrum!

1024
01:32:46,583 --> 01:32:48,643
Are you having a bad dream?

1025
01:32:54,593 --> 01:32:55,822
Hon?

1026
01:33:01,634 --> 01:33:05,537
Danny's not here, Mrs. Torrance.

1027
01:33:10,545 --> 01:33:12,070
Come on, hon.

1028
01:33:13,049 --> 01:33:14,482
Wake up.

1029
01:33:15,418 --> 01:33:17,682
You just had a bad dream.

1030
01:33:19,088 --> 01:33:21,216
Everything's okay.

1031
01:33:25,295 --> 01:33:29,164
Danny can't wake up, Mrs. Torrance.

1032
01:33:38,645 --> 01:33:40,442
Wake up!

1033
01:33:41,615 --> 01:33:42,947
Come on.

1034
01:33:43,150 --> 01:33:44,674
Right now.

1035
01:33:45,152 --> 01:33:46,517
Wake up!

1036
01:33:50,560 --> 01:33:54,587
Danny's gone away, Mrs. Torrance.

1037
01:34:04,708 --> 01:34:07,576
This is KDK 1 calling
KDK 12.

1038
01:34:07,779 --> 01:34:10,714
KDK 1 calling KDK 12.

1039
01:34:11,017 --> 01:34:12,780
Are you receiving me?

1040
01:34:15,989 --> 01:34:19,447
This is KDK 1 calling
KDK 12.

1041
01:34:19,793 --> 01:34:22,592
KDK 1 calling KDK 12.

1042
01:34:22,797 --> 01:34:24,458
Do you read me?

1043
01:34:28,836 --> 01:34:31,863
This is KDK 1 calling
KDK 12.

1044
01:34:32,075 --> 01:34:34,635
KDK 1 calling KDK 12.

1045
01:34:34,844 --> 01:34:36,607
Are you receiving me?

1046
01:35:13,056 --> 01:35:14,921
Good evening. Forest service.

1047
01:35:15,125 --> 01:35:17,356
This is Dick Hallorann again.

1048
01:35:17,562 --> 01:35:20,656
I called a while ago about
the folks at the Overlook Hotel.

1049
01:35:21,899 --> 01:35:25,700
We tried to contact them several
times but they didn't answer.

1050
01:35:25,904 --> 01:35:29,499
Maybe they got their radio
turned off or they can't hear it.

1051
01:35:29,708 --> 01:35:32,610
If you'd like, I'd be glad
to try again later on.

1052
01:35:33,114 --> 01:35:35,241
That's very nice of you.

1053
01:35:35,449 --> 01:35:37,212
I'll call you back later.

1054
01:35:37,418 --> 01:35:38,442
Bye.

1055
01:36:25,541 --> 01:36:28,568
Pardon me, miss.
What time will we get to Denver?

1056
01:36:28,778 --> 01:36:30,939
We're due to arrive at 8:20, sir.

1057
01:36:31,147 --> 01:36:32,739
Thank you very much.

1058
01:37:36,659 --> 01:37:37,591
Durkin's Garage.

1059
01:37:37,793 --> 01:37:38,919
Can I speak to Larry?

1060
01:37:39,128 --> 01:37:40,095
Speaking.

1061
01:37:40,396 --> 01:37:42,887
Hi, Larry. This is Dick.
Dick Hallorann.

1062
01:37:43,165 --> 01:37:44,827
Dick! How you doing?

1063
01:37:45,035 --> 01:37:46,400
How's the weather down there?

1064
01:37:46,603 --> 01:37:49,766
I'm not in Florida.
I'm calling from Stapleton Airport.

1065
01:37:50,140 --> 01:37:51,732
What are you doing there?

1066
01:37:52,176 --> 01:37:55,612
I just got in from Miami.
I got to get to the Overlook today.

1067
01:37:55,814 --> 01:37:57,441
What's the weather like there?

1068
01:37:58,083 --> 01:38:00,951
The snowplows are keeping things
moving in town...

1069
01:38:01,154 --> 01:38:03,088
...but the mountain roads
are blocked.

1070
01:38:03,623 --> 01:38:06,319
Then I'm going to need a Snowcat
to get up there.

1071
01:38:06,526 --> 01:38:08,358
Can you fix me up with one?

1072
01:38:08,562 --> 01:38:10,655
What's the big deal
about getting there today...

1073
01:38:10,865 --> 01:38:12,423
...especially in this weather?

1074
01:38:13,301 --> 01:38:16,760
Larry, just between you and me,
we got a very serious problem...

1075
01:38:16,973 --> 01:38:19,203
...with the people taking care
of the place.

1076
01:38:19,409 --> 01:38:23,278
They turned out to be
completely unreliable assholes.

1077
01:38:23,480 --> 01:38:25,277
Ullman phoned me last night.

1078
01:38:25,482 --> 01:38:28,849
And I'm supposed to find out
if they have to be replaced.

1079
01:38:30,321 --> 01:38:32,347
How long will it take you
to get here?

1080
01:38:32,691 --> 01:38:34,352
About five hours.

1081
01:38:34,559 --> 01:38:36,789
I'm going to rent a car
here at the airport.

1082
01:38:37,296 --> 01:38:39,026
Okay, I'll take care of it.

1083
01:38:39,232 --> 01:38:42,065
Thanks, Larry.
I really appreciate that.

1084
01:38:42,269 --> 01:38:44,829
That's all right. Drive carefully.

1085
01:38:50,578 --> 01:38:53,843
You're with Hal and Charlie
on Radio 63, KHOW, Denver.

1086
01:38:54,048 --> 01:38:56,609
And we have a bad day out there.

1087
01:38:56,819 --> 01:39:00,186
Heavy snow throughout
the Denver metro area.

1088
01:39:00,390 --> 01:39:01,880
Many mountain passes...

1089
01:39:02,092 --> 01:39:04,960
... Wolf Creek and Red Mountain
passes are closed...

1090
01:39:05,162 --> 01:39:08,461
...and the chain law is in effect
at the Eisenhower Tunnel.

1091
01:39:08,666 --> 01:39:10,328
We hear from the news department...

1092
01:39:10,535 --> 01:39:13,732
...only a few flights are
landing at Stapleton Airport...

1093
01:39:13,939 --> 01:39:15,531
...and with storms like this...

1094
01:39:15,741 --> 01:39:19,872
...I guess the entire airport will
be closed within the hour.

1095
01:39:20,047 --> 01:39:22,914
The storm will continue through
the day and the Weather Service...

1096
01:39:23,117 --> 01:39:25,586
...has declared a stockman's
and traveler's advisory...

1097
01:39:25,787 --> 01:39:28,585
...for all areas outlying
the Denver metro region.

1098
01:39:28,790 --> 01:39:30,155
Get the cows in the barn.

1099
01:39:51,650 --> 01:39:52,708
Hon?

1100
01:39:57,690 --> 01:40:00,124
Listen to me
for a minute, will you?

1101
01:40:03,931 --> 01:40:07,629
I'm just going to go and
talk to Daddy for a few minutes...

1102
01:40:07,836 --> 01:40:09,861
...and I'll be right back.

1103
01:40:10,839 --> 01:40:13,365
I want you to just stay here...

1104
01:40:13,576 --> 01:40:16,067
...and watch your cartoons, okay?

1105
01:40:19,183 --> 01:40:20,651
Okay, hon?

1106
01:40:23,955 --> 01:40:26,822
Yes, Mrs. Torrance.

1107
01:40:35,601 --> 01:40:36,796
All right.

1108
01:40:38,872 --> 01:40:41,773
I'll be back
in just about five minutes.

1109
01:40:42,577 --> 01:40:44,910
I'm going to lock the door
behind me.

1110
01:44:11,289 --> 01:44:12,984
How do you like it?

1111
01:44:19,598 --> 01:44:21,122
How do you like it?

1112
01:44:31,079 --> 01:44:33,741
What are you doing down here?

1113
01:44:38,121 --> 01:44:40,453
I just...

1114
01:44:40,923 --> 01:44:41,947
...wanted...

1115
01:44:42,392 --> 01:44:44,121
...to talk to you.

1116
01:44:46,498 --> 01:44:47,760
Okay.

1117
01:44:48,366 --> 01:44:49,833
Let's talk.

1118
01:44:59,645 --> 01:45:01,637
What do you want to talk about?

1119
01:45:09,558 --> 01:45:12,721
I can't really remember.

1120
01:45:13,529 --> 01:45:15,656
You can't remember.

1121
01:45:16,466 --> 01:45:17,797
No...

1122
01:45:18,168 --> 01:45:19,567
...I can't.

1123
01:45:24,875 --> 01:45:28,140
Maybe it was about Danny?

1124
01:45:30,515 --> 01:45:33,212
Maybe it was about him.

1125
01:45:36,856 --> 01:45:40,156
I think we should discuss Danny.

1126
01:45:42,963 --> 01:45:44,760
I think...

1127
01:45:45,165 --> 01:45:48,932
...we should discuss
what should be done with him.

1128
01:45:53,642 --> 01:45:56,237
What should be done with him?

1129
01:46:01,218 --> 01:46:03,015
I don't know.

1130
01:46:03,521 --> 01:46:05,512
I don't think that's true.

1131
01:46:05,723 --> 01:46:08,317
I think you have some
very definite ideas...

1132
01:46:08,527 --> 01:46:10,222
...about what should be done
with Danny.

1133
01:46:10,429 --> 01:46:13,024
And I'd like to know
what they are.

1134
01:46:14,934 --> 01:46:16,731
Well, l...

1135
01:46:17,036 --> 01:46:21,440
...I think maybe he should be taken
to a doctor.

1136
01:46:21,642 --> 01:46:24,941
You think "maybe"
he should be taken to a doctor?

1137
01:46:27,182 --> 01:46:30,515
When do you think "maybe"
he should be taken to a doctor?

1138
01:46:31,153 --> 01:46:32,518
As soon as possible?

1139
01:46:33,122 --> 01:46:35,455
"As soon as possible?"

1140
01:46:38,128 --> 01:46:39,561
Please.

1141
01:46:40,964 --> 01:46:44,230
You believe his health
might be at stake.

1142
01:46:45,803 --> 01:46:47,327
Yes.

1143
01:46:48,674 --> 01:46:51,303
And you are concerned about him.

1144
01:46:53,880 --> 01:46:56,110
And are you concerned about me?

1145
01:46:56,950 --> 01:46:58,111
Of course I am.

1146
01:46:58,319 --> 01:47:00,549
Of course you are!

1147
01:47:00,755 --> 01:47:03,883
Have you ever thought about
my responsibilities?

1148
01:47:04,091 --> 01:47:05,582
What are you talking about?

1149
01:47:05,794 --> 01:47:08,627
Have you ever had
a single moment's...

1150
01:47:08,831 --> 01:47:10,890
...thought about
my responsibilities?

1151
01:47:11,100 --> 01:47:13,365
Have you ever thought
for a single moment...

1152
01:47:13,571 --> 01:47:16,369
...about my responsibilities
to my employers?!

1153
01:47:16,640 --> 01:47:18,471
Has is ever occurred to you...

1154
01:47:18,676 --> 01:47:22,169
...that I have agreed to look after
the hotel until May 1st?

1155
01:47:22,414 --> 01:47:24,439
Does it matter to you at all...

1156
01:47:24,649 --> 01:47:27,743
...that the owners have placed
their complete confidence in me...

1157
01:47:27,953 --> 01:47:31,082
...and that I have signed
a letter of agreement...

1158
01:47:31,291 --> 01:47:33,885
...in which I've accepted
that responsibility?

1159
01:47:34,361 --> 01:47:36,386
Do you have the slightest idea...

1160
01:47:36,597 --> 01:47:39,829
...what a moral and ethical
principal is? Do you?!

1161
01:47:40,201 --> 01:47:43,295
Has it ever occurred to you what
would happen to my future...

1162
01:47:43,504 --> 01:47:45,905
...if I fail to live up to
my responsibilities?

1163
01:47:46,108 --> 01:47:48,406
Has it ever occurred to you?
Has it?!

1164
01:47:48,611 --> 01:47:50,135
Stay away from me!

1165
01:47:51,014 --> 01:47:52,072
Why?

1166
01:47:52,383 --> 01:47:55,352
I just want to go back to my room.

1167
01:47:55,553 --> 01:47:56,815
Why?

1168
01:47:57,455 --> 01:47:58,319
Well...

1169
01:47:59,457 --> 01:48:01,483
...I'm very confused.

1170
01:48:02,628 --> 01:48:06,291
And I just need a chance
to think things over.

1171
01:48:07,332 --> 01:48:11,269
You've had your whole fucking life
to think things over!

1172
01:48:11,472 --> 01:48:14,236
What good's a few minutes more
going to do you now?

1173
01:48:15,209 --> 01:48:16,700
Stay away from me!

1174
01:48:17,045 --> 01:48:18,342
Please!

1175
01:48:19,114 --> 01:48:20,172
Don't hurt me.

1176
01:48:20,382 --> 01:48:21,713
I'm not going to hurt you.

1177
01:48:21,916 --> 01:48:23,110
Stay away from me!

1178
01:48:23,318 --> 01:48:24,183
Stay away!

1179
01:48:24,387 --> 01:48:25,376
Darling.

1180
01:48:25,588 --> 01:48:27,146
Light of my life.

1181
01:48:27,590 --> 01:48:28,921
I'm not going to hurt you.

1182
01:48:29,125 --> 01:48:31,116
You didn't let me finish
my sentence.

1183
01:48:31,329 --> 01:48:33,524
I said,
"I'm not going to hurt you."

1184
01:48:33,731 --> 01:48:36,495
I'm just going to bash
your brains in.

1185
01:48:36,768 --> 01:48:39,738
I'm going to bash them
right the fuck in.

1186
01:48:40,806 --> 01:48:42,364
Stay away from me!

1187
01:48:42,875 --> 01:48:43,899
Stay away from me!

1188
01:48:44,109 --> 01:48:46,509
I'm not going to hurt you.

1189
01:48:46,779 --> 01:48:48,304
Stay away from me!

1190
01:48:48,548 --> 01:48:49,606
Stay away!

1191
01:48:50,483 --> 01:48:51,711
Please!

1192
01:48:52,753 --> 01:48:54,516
Stop swinging the bat.

1193
01:48:54,723 --> 01:48:55,985
Stay away from me.

1194
01:48:56,758 --> 01:48:58,055
Put that bat down, Wendy.

1195
01:48:58,260 --> 01:48:59,750
Stop it!

1196
01:49:01,229 --> 01:49:02,355
Give me the bat.

1197
01:49:02,565 --> 01:49:03,691
Please!

1198
01:49:03,933 --> 01:49:06,128
- Stay away!
- Give me the bat.

1199
01:49:06,335 --> 01:49:07,393
Stop it!

1200
01:49:07,637 --> 01:49:09,070
Give me the bat.

1201
01:49:09,405 --> 01:49:11,033
- Stay away from me.
- Stop swinging the bat.

1202
01:49:11,241 --> 01:49:12,606
Please stop!

1203
01:49:12,811 --> 01:49:14,005
Give me the bat.

1204
01:49:14,212 --> 01:49:15,440
Stay away from me.

1205
01:49:15,714 --> 01:49:18,081
- Stop it!
- Give me the bat.

1206
01:49:19,485 --> 01:49:20,509
Goddamn--!

1207
01:50:35,808 --> 01:50:37,504
What are you doing?

1208
01:50:40,313 --> 01:50:41,780
Wait a minute.

1209
01:50:43,183 --> 01:50:45,175
What are you doing?

1210
01:50:48,022 --> 01:50:49,250
What are you doing?

1211
01:51:03,140 --> 01:51:04,630
Wait a minute!

1212
01:51:07,010 --> 01:51:08,603
What are you doing?

1213
01:51:08,847 --> 01:51:10,576
Open the door!

1214
01:51:11,883 --> 01:51:12,907
Goddamn it!

1215
01:51:13,117 --> 01:51:16,679
Let me out of here!
Open the goddamn door!

1216
01:51:20,393 --> 01:51:21,621
Wendy, listen.

1217
01:51:22,062 --> 01:51:24,998
Let me out and I'll forget
the whole goddamn thing.

1218
01:51:25,199 --> 01:51:27,667
It'll be just like
nothing ever happened.

1219
01:51:42,353 --> 01:51:43,718
Baby.

1220
01:51:44,922 --> 01:51:48,222
I think you hurt my head
real bad.

1221
01:51:49,828 --> 01:51:51,489
I'm dizzy.

1222
01:51:52,497 --> 01:51:54,693
I need a doctor.

1223
01:52:01,575 --> 01:52:02,770
Honey.

1224
01:52:05,446 --> 01:52:07,778
Don't leave me in here.

1225
01:52:16,393 --> 01:52:18,294
I'm going to go now.

1226
01:52:21,365 --> 01:52:23,196
I'm going to try...

1227
01:52:23,401 --> 01:52:26,394
...to get Danny down
the Sidewinder...

1228
01:52:27,105 --> 01:52:29,471
...in the Snowcat today.

1229
01:52:31,710 --> 01:52:33,542
I'll bring back a doctor.

1230
01:52:38,919 --> 01:52:40,785
I'm going to go now.

1231
01:52:48,229 --> 01:52:52,030
You've got a big surprise
coming to you.

1232
01:52:53,502 --> 01:52:56,096
You're not going anywhere.

1233
01:52:57,775 --> 01:53:01,905
Go check out the Snowcat and the
radio, and you'll see what I mean.

1234
01:53:06,518 --> 01:53:08,213
Go check it out.

1235
01:53:10,356 --> 01:53:12,552
Go check it out!

1236
01:53:15,929 --> 01:53:17,863
Go check it out.

1237
01:55:05,725 --> 01:55:08,125
It's Grady, Mr. Torrance.

1238
01:55:08,863 --> 01:55:10,831
Delbert Grady.

1239
01:55:12,399 --> 01:55:13,991
Grady?

1240
01:55:34,359 --> 01:55:36,190
Hello, Grady.

1241
01:55:40,867 --> 01:55:42,664
Mr. Torrance...

1242
01:55:44,604 --> 01:55:48,336
...I see you can hardly
have taken care of the...

1243
01:55:49,076 --> 01:55:51,567
...business we discussed.

1244
01:55:58,287 --> 01:56:01,222
No need to rub it in, Mr. Grady.

1245
01:56:02,091 --> 01:56:06,153
I'll deal with that situation
as soon as I get out of here.

1246
01:56:07,031 --> 01:56:09,761
Will you indeed, Mr. Torrance?

1247
01:56:10,267 --> 01:56:12,099
I wonder.

1248
01:56:13,271 --> 01:56:15,364
I have my doubts.

1249
01:56:16,575 --> 01:56:20,808
I, and others, have come
to believe...

1250
01:56:21,013 --> 01:56:24,005
...that your heart is not in this.

1251
01:56:24,651 --> 01:56:27,177
That you haven't the belly for it.

1252
01:56:33,361 --> 01:56:37,662
Just give me one more chance
to prove it, Mr. Grady.

1253
01:56:38,500 --> 01:56:40,434
That's all I ask.

1254
01:56:41,972 --> 01:56:46,239
Your wife appears to be stronger
than we imagined, Mr. Torrance.

1255
01:56:46,444 --> 01:56:47,911
Somewhat more...

1256
01:56:48,112 --> 01:56:50,080
...resourceful.

1257
01:56:50,349 --> 01:56:53,113
She seems to have got
the better of you.

1258
01:56:56,355 --> 01:56:59,018
For the moment, Mr. Grady.

1259
01:56:59,759 --> 01:57:01,920
Only for the moment.

1260
01:57:03,831 --> 01:57:07,996
I fear you will have to deal
with this matter...

1261
01:57:08,270 --> 01:57:11,933
...in the harshest possible way,
Mr. Torrance.

1262
01:57:12,507 --> 01:57:14,066
I fear...

1263
01:57:14,343 --> 01:57:16,903
...that is the only thing to do.

1264
01:57:20,383 --> 01:57:22,477
There's nothing
I look forward to...

1265
01:57:22,686 --> 01:57:26,588
...with greater pleasure,
Mr. Grady.

1266
01:57:27,992 --> 01:57:30,723
You give your word on that,
do you, Mr. Torrance?

1267
01:57:32,197 --> 01:57:34,222
I give you my word.

1268
01:58:46,351 --> 01:58:48,912
Redrum.

1269
01:58:49,856 --> 01:58:52,416
Redrum.

1270
02:01:00,409 --> 02:01:01,967
Danny, stop it!

1271
02:01:58,777 --> 02:02:00,244
I'm home.

1272
02:02:37,590 --> 02:02:40,457
Come out, come out,
wherever you are.

1273
02:03:06,023 --> 02:03:07,888
I can't get out.

1274
02:03:08,693 --> 02:03:09,819
Run!

1275
02:03:10,661 --> 02:03:12,094
Run and hide!

1276
02:03:12,632 --> 02:03:13,758
Run!

1277
02:03:13,966 --> 02:03:15,194
Quick!

1278
02:03:16,903 --> 02:03:21,432
Little pigs, little pigs,
let me come in.

1279
02:03:27,181 --> 02:03:30,583
Not by the hair
on your chinny-chin-chin?

1280
02:03:32,121 --> 02:03:34,180
Then I'll huff...

1281
02:03:34,390 --> 02:03:36,291
...and I'll puff...

1282
02:03:36,493 --> 02:03:38,552
...and I'll blow your house in!

1283
02:03:53,480 --> 02:03:54,845
Please!

1284
02:03:55,582 --> 02:03:57,345
Don't!

1285
02:03:58,017 --> 02:03:59,542
Don't!

1286
02:04:18,142 --> 02:04:19,370
Stop it!

1287
02:04:23,615 --> 02:04:25,173
Here's Johnny!

1288
02:07:07,140 --> 02:07:08,368
Hello?

